Concluding ideas

In the beginning of collecting the data, the time spent on our phone is 5.9166667, and the average for the last rows of data collected is 7.1666667. While for the first rows of data collected, we can see that the average for how often we picked up our phone is 7.4166667, and for the last rows collected our average is 8.25.

By adding data from my friends I am able to compare their phone usage in comparison to me and my brother. This comparison is very insightful and helps us understand how phone usage differs between people. From the graphs we are able to see in the beginning YouTube and Instagram are the most used apps, but when comparing it to the end TikTok and Imessages are the most used apps. We can also see that the data collected between me and my friends show that the average time spent is six hours or less and only a couple of times has it excceded to eleven or twelve hours.

By adding in my friends data on how they use their phone me and my brother are able to conclude that our phone usage is much higher and that its is a very unhealthy habit; my friends were also very interested and shocked by their phone usage as well because they havent put much thought into how often or how long they spent on their phones prior to this to my study.

Overall this was very interesting and also enjoyable as it allowed me to be more insightful of my screen time and also gave me the oppertunity to have a conversation about phone useage with my friends giving them insight.
